widgets_values: Extra loading methods (GGUF is generally the fastest) - Connect to the other nodes in the group if you want to use.

Base Schnell generation gets sharpened & passed to upscaler and detailer.

Make sure your detailer model matches the style of image you want to make. (Anime = deblur) (Realistic = skin) etc.

------  Flux VALHALLA Starter Edition  ------

--  by @ericreator  --

-- Digital Creative --

-- http://ericmotion.com -- https://x.com/ericreator --
______________________________________________

This workflow is for beginners to easily get ComfyUI working on their Windows machines. It features the latest technology and efficiency research

VALHALLA is a highly efficient 100% FLUX Schnell workflow focused on providing optimized quality and speed options using minimal VRAM.

Load, refine, and upscale with your favorite GGUF and safetensors models.

It's heavily annotated so intermediate and beginner users can follow along.

Check out the WIP extended edition if you want more functionality.

https://civitai.com/images/32622819


>>> If you want the best experience - match my models <<<

Published: October 2024

CREDITS:

Tenofas - Modular Flux 
https://civitai.com/models/642589?modelVersionId=820435

Tenofas - Latent Detailing
https://civitai.com/models/719931?modelVersionId=805023

nerdyrodent - Latent upscale
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PRiqTnP3no8&t=193s

JockerAI - 1 step Flux upscale trick!
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oVnTZLRgUC0&t=248s

Loading GGUF's here of model and text encoder. Lower Q's will use less VRAM at a slight tradeoff of quality.

T5 Text encoder Q3_K_L works fine and is fast.

ClipL and VAE are the same as FLUX dev.

Nerdyrodent does this force device thing I just copied it I guess it's good.

Next we upscale and add skin texture with models.

https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-SkinContrast-High-SuperUltraCompact

https://openmodeldb.info/models/2x-NomosUni-compact-otf-medium

(Fast and modern 2x)

Then we lower the size by 20% to make Valhalla faster. You may need to go lower if your VRAM can't handle Valhalla.
Lastly we add one more pass of skin grain, sharpen and save. Voila!

LORAS - Flux Dev ones mostly work. (NOT HYPER) Put the identity ones on top and don't mix too many. ID loras and style ones don't mix too well. Use trigger words in prompt. Definitely experiment here.

Controlnet and IPadapter are too slow for this workflow. You can add them here if you have power.

Check out the WIP extended edition if you want more functionality.

Finally! VALHALLA!

This part of workflow adds a ton of great detail with a double sampler. First sampler to fix the general anatomy and details, and then the second one is at a lower denoise for photorealism and to eliminate artifacts. Feel free to adjust. I like heunpp2 for fixing details.

Steps Usually just 1. If you want to maximize quality and details, increase denoise and steps.

Denoise usually 0.08 - 0.2 but you can tweak it.

Higher denoise will turn it painterly and change the face and eventually the whole composition.

If you see scanline or grid type artifacts, ajusting samplers and denoise here can help reduce and remove them.

Put your prompt here. Negatives do not work. Describe everything you want to see in the image. It can handle a like 5 independent concepts before it starts getting pretty confused & text will degrade.

Some Loras require their trigger words. "egmid" is for Midjourney_Anime

Common Resolutions - You can use any size really.
256px up to 1536px

1024 x 1024 (1:1 Square)
1152 x 896 (9:7)
896 x 1152 (7:9)
1216 x 832 (19:13)
832 x 1216 (13:19)
1344 x 768 (7:4 Horizontal)
768 x 1344 (4:7 Vertical)
1536 x 640 (12:5 Horizontal)
640 x 1536 (5:12 Vertical)

Guidance control - Guidance has NO effect.
Clip_L also. They are both random noise.

Samplers - LCM for speed. Others are ok but not as fast.

ModelSamplingFlux does something but idk.

Beta scheduler seems to be the highest quality but there are slightly faster ones.

Steps can be 2-4, higher not really necessary imo but 3 and 4 have less anatomy errors. Image quality comes from the second pass.

I like to explore at 4 step Thor only and then upscale the seeds I like by dragging them into the workflow.

Seeds - Keep them fixed if you want a fixed gen.

Batches - I ran a batch of 4, it crashed on the upscaler for me. Keep it to 2 or 1 unless you're using low res or have more compute.

Resolution- Works with any sdxl resolution. Weird stuff starsts to happen with irregular aspect ratios and 2k+ sizes.

clip_scale is multiplied by dimensions to give final base image size. Higher than SDXL resolutin gets slow and hyperdetailed. 0.5 - 1.5
!!! Resolution and number of steps in samplers are the best ways to trade quality for speed !!!
